# @Injectable() üíâ

Generated with `ng g service hero`.

```typescript
import { Injectable } from '@angular/core';

@Injectable({
  providedIn: 'root',
})
export class HeroService {
  getHeroes() { return ['Superman', 'Batman']; }
}
```

# Fetching Data üåê

Angular's `HttpClient` returns **Observables** (from RxJS).

```typescript
constructor(private http: HttpClient) {}

getUsers() {
  return this.http.get<User[]>('/api/users');
}
```
Don't forget to import `HttpClientModule` in `app.module.ts`.

# usage in Component üì∫

Observables are lazy. Nothing happens until you `.subscribe()`.

```typescript
ngOnInit() {
  this.userService.getUsers().subscribe(data => {
    this.users = data;
  });
}
```

